title.narrative: 4.2 PUBLIC FINANCE FOR CHILDREN

description.narrative: Public expenditure in social sectors is regularly monitored to ensure adequacy, efficiency and equity for children needs., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Economic And Social Policy General, Public Finance And Local Governance, Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, child poverty and well-being are regularly monitored, and social policies, especially social protection systems, are strengthened to favour the social inclusion of vulnerable girls and boys at the national and decentralized levels.

title.narrative: Public expenditure in social sectors is regularly monitored to ensure adequacy, efficiency and equity for children needs.

description.narrative: Capacity building on Public Finances for Children (PF4C) was ensured, in collaboration with the Ministry of Economy and Finance (MoEF), for the benefit of the main actors working in childhood issues. A strategic and operational inter-ministerial technical committee in charge of Child-Sensitive Budgeting (CSB) has been set up and a roadmap for monitoring and implementing the CSB approach has been made. Specific PF4C analyzes were carried out, especially the preschool costing and the strategy and sustainability of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). These interventions are part of the PF4C strategy of UNICEF Morocco,adopted in 2021 with a participatory approach. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2022
